 Health Monitoring System for Elderly
Problem Statement:
Elderly people often live alone and lack immediate access to
health monitoring and emergency alerts.
Objective:
Create a system that monitors pulse rate, temperature, and fall
detection, and sends alerts if abnormalities are detected.
Requirements:
NodeMCU ESP8266
Pulse Sensor
DHT11 Sensor
MPU6050 Accelerometer (for fall detection)
Blynk or ThingSpeak
Expected Outcome:
A compact wearable system that sends health status and
emergency alerts to caregivers or medical professionals.

